# Status Update terminal rule (P26 §3b + agile)

When you emit a **Status Update**, it is the **end of your message**. Stop typing after `### Approval needed` (or after `### Next work item` if approval is none).

## Required sections (in order)

1. **`### Execution mode`** — verb + mode id + scope + completion rates (from `agent:next-work` JSON `execution` / `progress`)
2. **`### Done`** — evidence-linked outcomes
3. **`### Next work item`** — **Type** (Epic/Story/Task/Sprint/Milestone) + **ID** + owner — **not** "Next priority"
4. **`### Approval needed`** — Class A/S only; omit if empty

Run `pnpm agent:next-work` before closing. Use `nextWorkItem.typeLabel`, `nextWorkItem.id`, `statusUpdateSections`.

## Next work item = exactly one agile artifact

| Mode | Next type should be |
| ---- | ------------------- |
| `complete_sprint` | Story or Task in **current sprint** |
| `complete_all_sprints` | Story or Task; progress = sprints sealed |
| `complete_roadmap` | Epic/Feature for icebox; Story when in-flight; Milestone when sealed |

- **Never** list two stories then ask which to do.
- When `backlogClear: true`: **Type: Milestone** · **State: complete** · list deferred epic if any.

## Hard-forbidden (after Status Update)

- `### Next priority` as the only orienting header (use **Execution mode** + **Next work item**)
- `Want me to proceed with … or …?`
- Any `?` asking operator to pick between two stories

## Class R

If **Next work item** is Class R and shell access exists: **begin that work** — do not ask permission.
